Description: Nine fragments of a dark brown, loosely woven, wool textile. The weave is plain, and the threads are 's'-spun and 's'-plied. The warp stitch gauge count is 8 per 10mm. The weft is 8 per 10mm.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Kulubnarti, 21-S-2 Outside north wall of F1
Condition: Poor condition, burned, crumbly, wadded and brittle.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Dr William Yewdale Adams
Donated by: W S Webb Museum of Anthropology (University of Kentucky)
Additional IDs: Excavation/small finds number: 85.2.106 (excavation object cat. no.)
